annotationA: Mummy, isoform A; Mummy (Mmy) is an UDP-N-acetylglucosamine diphosphorylase. It functions in apical extracellular matrix formation by producing GlcNAc residues needed for chitin synthesis and protein glycosylation. Mmy regulates cuticle production, tracheal morphogenesis, and axon guidance
annotationB: N-acetyltransferase activity; glucosamine 6-phosphate N-acetyltransferase activity; Belongs to the acetyltransferase family. GNA1 subfamily
